# Testing conventions

- Add tests next to existing ones in `tests/`. The suite must stay fast and run
  without external services (`conftest.py` isolates the environment).
- Integration tests that need Qdrant are named `tests/test_integration_*.py` and
  only run in CI's `integration` job.
- Coverage floor is 35% (`fail_under = 35`); ratchet up, never down.
- Don't import the same module two ways in one file (avoid CodeQL
  `py/import-and-import-from`): use `import mimir.cli` and reference
  `mimir.cli.app`, not a mix of `import` and `from ... import`.
- Run with `uv run pytest`. `make test` adds coverage.
